The application of a primary panel of antibodies to characterize tumor histogenesis (epithelial, mesenchymal, neural, or hematopoietic) is often the first step. When this panel has been established, additional antibodies can be used to identify the tumor type more specifically. Included in the first tier would be antibodies against pan-keratin, vimentin, S-100 protein, neuron-specific enolase (NSE) and CD45 (common leukocyte antigen) to differentiate epithelial, mesenchymal, melanomatous, neural, and lymphoid malignancies (Table 5-1
; Fig. 5-2
).
